    {
      "Module Name": "GPIO Pin Headers and Expansion Interface",
      "Function Description": "Provides standard pin headers that break out the ESP32's GPIO pins for easy breadboarding and connection to external peripherals, enabling flexible hardware expansion.",
      "Signal Sources": "GPIO signals from the ESP32-WROOM-32E module, including digital I/O, analog inputs, and communication interfaces.",
      "Signal Destinations": "External peripherals such as sensors, actuators, or other development boards connected via the pin headers.",
      "Implementation Logic": "Male or female pin headers are soldered to the board, with traces connecting each header pin to the corresponding GPIO pin on the ESP32-WROOM-32E, ensuring proper spacing and labeling for user accessibility.",
      "Signal Chain": "The GPIO Pin Headers and Expansion Interface module functions as a passive breakout board. GPIO signals from the ESP32-WROOM-32E module (including digital I/O, analog inputs, and communication interfaces like UART, SPI, I2C) are routed directly through traces to male or female pin headers. These headers provide physical access points for external peripherals such as sensors, actuators, or other development boards. The signal flow is linear: ESP32 GPIO pins → PCB traces → pin header pins → external connections. No active signal conditioning or protocol conversion is required; the module simply extends the ESP32's native interfaces for flexible hardware expansion.",
