    {
      "Module Name": "ESP32-WROOM-32E Core Module",
      "Function Description": "Provides the main microcontroller unit with integrated Wi-Fi and Bluetooth connectivity for IoT applications, handling data processing, communication, and control tasks.",
      "Signal Sources": "GPIO pins from the ESP32-WROOM-32E module, including UART signals from the CP2102N, I2C signals from the IMU, and power from the power management block.",
      "Signal Destinations": "GPIO pins to the pin headers for peripheral expansion, I2C signals to the IMU for communication, and internal processing for Wi-Fi/Bluetooth transmission.",
      "Implementation Logic": "The ESP32-WROOM-32E module is mounted on the board with its pins connected to the necessary circuits, including UART for serial communication via CP2102N, I2C for IMU interfacing, and power rails from the AMS1117-3.3 LDO.",
      "Signal Chain": "The ESP32-WROOM-32E module serves as the core microcontroller, powered by a 3.3V supply from the AMS1117 LDO regulator, which steps down from a 5V input via the Micro-USB connector. The CP2102N USB-to-UART bridge facilitates serial communication between the ESP32 and a host PC through the Micro-USB interface, with UART signals (TXD, RXD) connected bidirectionally. The LSM6DSMTR IMU communicates with the ESP32 via I2C for sensor data acquisition, using dedicated SDA and SCL lines. GPIO pins from the ESP32 are routed to pin headers for peripheral expansion, while internal processing handles Wi-Fi/Bluetooth transmission. Power management includes the AMS1117 for voltage regulation, with optional components like the 2N7002 MOSFET for switching control, BAT760 diode for protection, SS8050-G BJT for amplification, and SW tactile switch for user input, all integrated into the signal flow as needed for specific circuit functions.",
