      "Module Name": "Power Management and USB Interface",
      "Function Description": "Manages power supply by stepping down 5V from the Micro USB input to 3.3V for the MCU and IMU, and provides ESD-protected USB connectivity with serial conversion for debugging and communication.",
      "Signal Sources": "5V input from the Micro USB port, DTR and RTS signals from the CP2102N for automatic download control.",
      "Signal Destinations": "3.3V output to the ESP32-WROOM-32E and IMU, serial data signals to/from the CP2102N, and control signals to the automatic download circuit.",
      "Implementation Logic": "Uses an AMS1117-3.3 LDO to regulate 5V USB input to 3.3V, with ESD protection on the Micro USB lines. The CP2102N converts USB data to UART signals for the ESP32, and its DTR/RTS outputs drive the automatic download circuit.",
      "Signal Chain": "The Micro-USB connector (1050170001) provides 5V power (pin 1) and USB data signals (pins 2 and 3) from an external source. The 5V input is regulated to 3.3V by the AMS1117 LDO (pin 3 VIN to pin 2 VOUT), which supplies power to the ESP32 (pin 2 3V3) and IMU (pin 8 VDD). The USB data lines (D+ and D-) from the Micro-USB are connected to the CP2102N (pins 4 D+ and 5 D-) for ESD-protected USB-to-UART conversion. The CP2102N outputs UART signals: TXD (pin 26) to ESP32 RXD0 (pin 34) and RXD (pin 25) to ESP32 TXD0 (pin 35). The CP2102N's DTR (pin 28) and RTS (pin 24) control the automatic download circuit, which uses a 2N7002 MOSFET (pin 1 Gate connected to DTR/RTS via logic, pin 2 Drain to ESP32 EN, pin 3 Source to ground) to reset the ESP32. Ground connections are shared among all components via the Micro-USB pin 5, CP2102N pin 3, ESP32 pins 1, 15, 38, 39, and IMU pins 6, 7.",
